<subSubSection id="8EFE650CFFDBFF98FFDF8BE9FC0EFE82" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C65B3687FFDBFF98FFDF8BE9FC0EFE82" blockId="13.[111,649,1437,1699]" lastBlockId="13.[677,1211,215,265]" pageId="13" pageNumber="18">
DIAGNOSIS. — (Adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="A2754B76FFDBFF98FE3D8BE9FDCEFA3E" author="WERDING B." box="[403,543,1437,1461]" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" pagination="306 - 310" refId="ref18806" refString="WERDING B. 1996. - Description of a new porcellanid, Petrolisthes gertrudae from the southeastern Caribbean Sea (Crustacea: Decapoda: Porcellanidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109: 306 - 310, figs 1, 2." type="book chapter" year="1996">Werding 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Carapace smooth; supra-ocular and external orbital angles unarmed; epibranchial region unarmed.Carpus of cheliped anteriorly rounded, sometimes slightly denticulated on proximal portion; dorsal surface granulated; posterior margin unarmed. Palm of cheliped granulated on dorsal surface; anterior and posterior margins unarmed; anterior margin with thick tuft of long setae, not extended onto fixed finger; gape of fingers without pubescence. Ambulatory legs unarmed and devoid of setae on anterior margins; dactylus with four movable spines on posterior margin. Telson composed of seven plates
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8EFE650CFFDBFF98FD0B8F55FC75FDDC" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C65B3687FFDBFF98FD0B8F55FB7AFE79" blockId="13.[677,1211,289,498]" pageId="13" pageNumber="18">
REMARKS. — Although 
<taxonomicName id="01E44D04FFDBFF98FC3A8F56FBD2FEB2" authorityName="Werding" authorityYear="1996" box="[916,1027,289,313]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gertrudae">
<emphasis id="F490EA95FFDBFF98FC3A8F56FBD2FEB2" box="[916,1027,289,313]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="18">P. gertrudae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="BEF37617FFDBFF98FC858F4FFC3AFED8" box="[811,1003,315,339]" name="Guadeloupe Island" pageId="13" pageNumber="18">Guadeloupe Island</collectingCountry>
, it was not retrieved during KARUBENTHOS. It cannot be confused with any of the other porcellanid species recognized during the expedition based on the armatures on the carapace, cheliped and ambulatory legs, and the noticeable thick tufts of long setae covering the anterior margin of the palm of the cheliped (see 
<bibRefCitation id="A2754B76FFDBFF98FC308FAEFBB1FE79" author="WERDING B." box="[926,1120,474,498]" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" pagination="306 - 310" refId="ref18806" refString="WERDING B. 1996. - Description of a new porcellanid, Petrolisthes gertrudae from the southeastern Caribbean Sea (Crustacea: Decapoda: Porcellanidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109: 306 - 310, figs 1, 2." type="book chapter" year="1996">Werding 1996: 307</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C65B3687FFDBFF98FD0B8C7EFC75FDDC" blockId="13.[677,1211,522,599]" pageId="13" pageNumber="18">
HABITAT. — Living on the exposed reef of the upper littoral region, in colony of zoanthid coral 
<taxonomicName id="01E44D04FFDBFF98FBCF8C50FC71FDDC" authority="(Werding, 1996)" baseAuthorityName="Werding" baseAuthorityYear="1996" class="Anthozoa" family="Zoanthidae" genus="Zoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis id="F490EA95FFDBFF98FBCF8C50FD22FDDC" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="18">Zoanthus fasciatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A2754B76FFDBFF98FD518C4BFC49FDDC" author="WERDING B." box="[767,920,575,599]" pageId="13" pageNumber="18" pagination="306 - 310" refId="ref18806" refString="WERDING B. 1996. - Description of a new porcellanid, Petrolisthes gertrudae from the southeastern Caribbean Sea (Crustacea: Decapoda: Porcellanidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109: 306 - 310, figs 1, 2." type="book chapter" year="1996">Werding, 1996</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
